'''''Tutaminis''''' was an umbrella title used by the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]] to classify [[The Force/Legends|Force]] [[Force power/Legends|abilities]] related to energy absorption. Designated as one in a family of ''Control'' abilities, ''tutaminis'' techniques were taught to [[Jedi Initiate/Legends|Jedi Initiates]] within the [[Jedi academy]] throughout the history of the Order. While taught to all [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] during the days of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], it was a rare feat to be capable of dissipating concentrated energy such as what makes up a [[Blaster/Legends|blasterbolt]] or [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] blade. While it was named and practiced by the Jedi Order, ''tutaminis'' was not restricted to use by Jedi. In fact, most [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-based groups]] and Force-users in general learned to use or at least control some of the abilities taught at the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Temple]].

==Overview==
[[File:Force_Absorb_JATM.jpg|thumb|left|200px|A [[Kel Dor/Legends|Kel Dor]] [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] absorbs blaster fire and channels it into Force lightning.]]
The skills associated with ''tutaminis'' all related to the idea that, through the Force, Force users could draw potentially harmful heat or electrical energy into their bodies and diffuse it or channel it away completely. Viewed as a starting point for further study in the Force, the [[Council of First Knowledge/Legends|Council of First Knowledge]] designated the study of ''tutaminis'' to be taught during the very first classes at Jedi academies. While the basics were expected to be mastered upon graduation from the academy, development of these skills would come over an entire life time, for a Jedi was never done learning.<ref name="TJP" /> In addition to deflecting energy weapons, this ability could eliminate the harmful effects of other energy-based Force powers such as [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]]. With additional effort, after absorbing a blaster bolt or Force power, the user could utilize the absorbed energy to heal his or her wounds or manifest other Force powers. ''Tutaminis'' was also described as a "non-harmful [[Force drain/Legends|Force drain]]."

The power could also be used to absorb or dissipate different types of energy, including light, heat, microwave or electromagnetic [[Radiation/Legends|radiation]], forms of hard radiation such as alpha, beta and gamma rays, and [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] fire.<ref name="RPG" />

==Accompanying skills==
[[File:TashaRyoTutaminis-ForceStorm2.jpg|thumb|right|200px|[[Tasha Ryo]] using tutaminis to deflect projectiles ("[[Slug/Legends|slugs]]").]]
As the basis of many abilities, ''tutaminis'' included many skills that were given proper or common names within the Jedi Order. Other abilities stem from this skill but were more personalized and not taught throughout the entire academy, if at all. Many skills, such as a simple body shielding or as advanced as catching and/or dispelling a [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] blade with one's bare hand, were all considered applications of ''tutaminis''.<ref name="TJP" />

Mastery in self-protection would include the capability to encase oneself in an energy field that could drain heat and electrical energy from incoming attacks. This ability would make the bearer invulnerable to kinetic and a wide range of energy-based attacks until the user discontinued its use, or it wore off when the user became fatigued. With this skill, it was possible to deflect blaster bolts with one's bare hands, though mastery of this skill was very difficult.<ref name="TJP" />

==Notable uses throughout history==
{{Quote|Much to learn you still have.|[[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] to [[Count/Legends|Count]] [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]], after absorbing his Force lightning|<ref name="AOTC" />}}
[[File:YodaCatch-hd.jpg|thumb|left|200px|[[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] Yoda absorbing [[Dooku/Legends|Darth Tyranus']] [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]].]]
While practiced by all Jedi during the Old Republic and essentially all Force-based cults to some extent, there were many individuals that excelled in this particular skill and are worthy of note. A member of the Jedi Order, not unlike many of his family members, [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Nejaa Halcyon]] developed this skill so as to make up for his lack of [[Telekinesis/Legends|telekinetic abilities]]. A virtuoso with the Force, Halcyon showed great talent in using ''tutaminis'' to absorb, redirect, and utilize heat and electrical energy discharges, often converting the energy he absorbed to utilize telekinetic powers that were usually beyond his talents.<ref name="Jedi Trial">''[[Jedi Trial]]''</ref> [[Darth/Legends|Darth]] [[Darth Plagueis/Legends|Plagueis]] also used this power while on board the ''[[Woebegone]]''. He was able to absorb the crew's blaster bolts in one hand and transferred the energy across his chest into Force lightning emerging from the other hand.<ref name="Star Wars: Darth Plagueis">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref>

Nejaa Halcyon's abilities in this power were such that he was able to catch lightsaber blades with his hand, an extremely rare talent that was also exhibited by [[Satele Shan]] who fought in the [[Battle of Alderaan]] during the [[Great Galactic War]] against the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]], [[Darth Malgus]].<ref name="Hope">{{TORweb|url=info/media/trailers/hope-cinematic-trailer|text="Hope"|int=Hope (cinematic trailer)}}</ref> Halcyon's descendant, [[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn]], later demonstrated similar talents, using the power to absorb heat energy from a volcanic spring on [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] to momentarily bolster his [[Telekinesis/Legends|telekinesis]]. Horn later utilized this ability to absorb the shock from a [[Stun baton/Legends|stun baton]] while aboard the ''[[Errant Venture/Legends|Errant Venture]]''. He then demonstrated the full extent of his talent while on [[Courkrus]], where he absorbed the heat energy from a series of explosions and redirected it to project a powerful [[Mind trick/Legends#Force illusion|Force Illusion]].<ref name="I, Jedi">''[[I, Jedi]]''</ref> Horn also demonstrated advanced use of the talents during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]] while on [[Bimmiel/Legends|Bimmiel]].<ref name="Onslaught">''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Tide I: Onslaught]]''</ref> [[Anakin Solo]] also demonstrated this variation of ''tutaminis'' when trapped on Yavin 4 later in the war.<ref name="Conquest">''[[The New Jedi Order: Edge of Victory I: Conquest]]''</ref>

[[Darth Krayt]],<ref name="LegacyWar1">[[Legacy — War 1|''Legacy — War'' 1]]</ref> [[Darth Wyyrlok (III)|Darth Wyyrlok]],<ref name="Leg27">[[Legacy (2006) 27|''Legacy'' (2006) 27]]</ref> [[Karness Muur]],<ref name="LegacyVector12">[[Legacy (2006) 31|''Legacy'' (2006) 31]]</ref> [[Kyp Durron|Kyp Duron]],<ref name="Dark Journey">''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Journey]]''</ref> [[Grand Master/Legends|Grand Master]] [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]], [[Galen Marek]] and [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] were able to catch [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]] with their bare hands. The latter three could also [[Force deflection/Legends|deflect]] Force Lightning back to its source. Master Yoda used this ability to deflect a blast of Force lightning from Count [[Dooku/Legends|Dooku]] back at him on [[Geonosis/Legends|Geonosis]].<ref name="AOTC" /> Revan used this ability to deflect a powerful barrage of [[Force lightning/Legends#Force_storm|lightning]] back at [[Darth Nyriss]], incinerating her with her own power in the process.<ref name="TOR:Revan">''[[The Old Republic: Revan]]''</ref> 

On [[Mortis/Legends|Mortis]], [[Son/Legends|Son]] was also capable of using this ability, as he blocked [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker's]] lightsaber strikes with his arms without much effort. [[Father (Mortis)/Legends|Father]] was also able to exhibit this ability, holding Anakin's lightsaber by the blade without damage to his hand, before forcing it back into its hilt. The final member of [[The Ones/Legends|The Ones]], [[Daughter/Legends|Daughter]], was able to deflect and absorb the Son's crimson Force lightning. The Daughter also caught one of the lightning blasts and hurled it back at the Son.

During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] demonstrated this skill during his battle with [[Durge/Legends|Durge]] by deflecting the Bounty Hunter's flamethrower using nothing but the Force,<ref name="CW8">''{{CW|8}}''</ref> and then shortly after blocked blaster bolts from a [[Droideka/Legends|Droideka]].<ref name="CW9">''{{CW|9}}''</ref> Later, while chasing [[General/Legends|General]] [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous]] through [[Utapau/Legends|Utapau]], he absorbed the energy of the [[Cyborg/Legends|cyborg's]] [[Electrostaff/Legends|electrostaff]] with his own bare hands before snatching away the weapon.<ref name="ROTS">{{Film|III}}</ref> [[Shaak Ti/Legends|Shaak Ti]] also used this ability during a duel with Grievous by deflecting his lightsaber after she was disarmed.<ref name="CW20">''{{CW|20}}''</ref>

[[Galen Marek]] was also able to use this ability in his desperate battle against [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious]], though the Emperor was able to kill him in the end of the conflict.<ref name="TFU">''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed]]''</ref> Marek's [[Subject 1138|clone]] was also able to use this ability in his duel with Darth Vader, when he absorbed a naturally generated lightning strike and redirected it at the Sith Lord, defeating him.<ref name="TFUII">''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed II]]''</ref>

In addition, Darth Vader used this ability to absorb blaster bolts with his hands on several occasions,<ref name="ESB" /> though he could not produce Force lightning due to his [[Cybernetics/Legends|cybernetic limbs]].<ref name="DL:TRoDV">''[[Dark Lord: The Rise of Darth Vader]]''</ref>

[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], when Darth Sidious tortured him with Force lightning aboard the [[Death Star II/Legends|second Death Star]] during the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], defended himself with this ability. Although Luke was initially successful, Sidious' increasing intensity with the energy, combined with Luke's lack of training in repelling such an attack and being unable to summon his lightsaber, overpowered Luke in short order.<ref name="ROTJ novel">[[Star Wars: Return of the Jedi (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode VI: Return of the Jedi'' novelization]]</ref> By the time of the Dark Empire Crisis, Luke's skill with tutamentis had vastly improved, to the point where he could use the ability to shield himself from the blaster fire of an [[All Terrain Armored Transport/Legends|ATAT Walker]].<ref>''[[Dark Empire 1]]''</ref>

[[Lost Tribe of Sith]] members were able to not only absorb energy from blaster bolts by their palms,<ref name="Backlash" /> but also able to deflect it back as they would otherwise by lightsaber.<ref name="Vortex">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Vortex]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
In computer games, the name of the Force power varies slightly&mdash;in ''[[Dark Forces: Jedi Knight]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight II: Jedi Outcast]]'', the power is called '''Force absorb''', while in ''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Jedi Academy]]'', it is called '''Force absorption'''.

In terms of game mechanics, the ability to absorb energy adds more points to the user's [[Personal Force reservoir|Force pool]] when absorbing an attack. Force absorb manifests in at least one game as a blue aura, although this is likely an interface mechanic to allow the player to know when the power is active.

